    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>This observation aims to prove directly with ALMA that silicate dust does not efficiently form around oxygen-rich AGB stars with relatively low mass-loss rates.  We propose to observe a radial distribution of SiO molecules in a circumstellar envelope of a typical silicate-poor and alumina-rich AGB star, W Hya, and verify that a large amount of SiO molecules remains in the envelope beyond the silicate-forming region.  This observation will reveal the nature of unexpected silicate-poor and alumina-rich dust shells around many AGB stars and constrain a dust formation process around silicate-poor stars.  We observe 29SiO (J=8-7), CO (J=3-2), AlOH (J=11-10), and AlO (N=9-8) at band 7 simultaneously.  The total observing time is 4.7 hours.</prp:abstract>
